t. Sunoco has implemented safety precautions and procedures designed to prevent and mitigate catastrophic releases. Sunoco has active operating, maintenance, training and inspection procedures. Sunoco provides annual emergency response training to its employees. Sunoco's management is committed to the following:



- Preventing accidents;

- Training our employees in correct response procedures in the event of an accident;

- Participating in community emergency preparedness;

- Addressing any citizen concerns by fully explaining potential hazards associated with Sunoco operations and all steps being taken to prevent and mitigate accidents; and

- Being a good corporate citizen in Wayne County.



With these objectives in mind, the Risk Management Plan has been developed to provide information about our management of the risks associated with the flammable substance storage process. Above all, we stress our commitment to ensuring a safe working environment for our employees, our visitors and our community.
